Project 2 - E2EV Voting Design

- generate keypairs for RSA and Paillier, load voter registry (hash and salt each with Sha256)
- CLI prompts for first name, last name, SSN with hidden input
- credentials checked in the authentication server comparing the hashed ssn with stored salt against the registry
- sets voted bool to true so they cant double vote, and issues a random rsa signed token
- CLI displays poll and the voting runs locally
- encrypts vote with paillier encryption and then the ciphertext and signed token get sent to the ballot server
- cli stores ciphertext hash as the voters reciept
- verify rsa token signature, check if that token hasnt been used already
- homomorphically add to the running tally, so the ballot server never sees an unencypted vote
- append ciphertext hash to some public available bulletin board, so anyone can verify the final tally is correct
- server never has the private key so it cannot decrypt any individual ballot
- Final tally gets decrypted and published alongside all individual ciphertext hashes
- anyone can verify that the sum of the published ciphertexts matches the published encrypted tally
- anyone can verify that the bulletin board receipt matches their stored receipt